<p>villages etc with Church steeples quiet undamaged.   The enemy's line here was close &amp; we were fortunate enough to witness several of his strong points being shelled both by our guns and trench mortars.   The trench mortars were firing a new type of shell, about 160 lbs weight, with wings like a torpedo.   When fired we could see them quite plainly in the air soaring upwards and then descending on the target.   Several direct hits were scored and one I saw apparently landed near a tree as tree &amp; all went up into the air.   With the glasses one could see practically everything &amp; places as far as "Menin" could be seen.  It was indeed an unique position &amp; we certainly do here hold the dominating position.   After about an hour of it we dragged ourselves away but before going far an enemy</p>
